@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";
}

<div class="container">
    <main role="main" class="pb-3">
        <h1 class="text-center mb-4">All About Surfing</h1>

        <div class="row mb-4">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <img src="~/images/surfing1.jpg" alt="Surfing in Action" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <img src="~/images/surfing2.jpg" alt="Sunset Surfing" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm">
            </div>
        </div>

        <p class="lead">
            Surfing is more than just a sport; it's a lifestyle. It involves riding waves on a surfboard, and it’s one of the most exhilarating and challenging outdoor activities. Surfers seek the thrill of gliding across the waves, embracing nature, and living in the moment. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced surfer, the sport offers endless joy and adventure.
        </p>

        <h3>History of Surfing</h3>
        <p>
            Surfing originated in ancient Polynesia, with the first known surfers being Hawaiian royalty. Surfing was later popularized in the 20th century by pioneers like Duke Kahanamoku, who is often regarded as the father of modern surfing. Today, it has grown into a global sport enjoyed by millions of people.
        </p>

        <h3>Types of Surfing</h3>
        <p>
            There are various types of surfing, including traditional longboarding, shortboarding, and more extreme disciplines like big wave surfing and tow-in surfing. Each type offers different techniques and challenges, but they all require skill, balance, and a connection to the ocean.
        </p>

        <h3>Surfing Culture</h3>
        <p>
            Surfing has a rich culture that embraces freedom, adventure, and a love for the ocean. Surfers are known for their laid-back, positive attitude and their respect for nature. Surfing communities around the world often gather to share experiences, tips, and stories. Whether it's at a local beach or an international surf competition, the spirit of camaraderie is always present.
        </p>

        <h3>Why Surf?</h3>
        <p>
            Surfing offers an incredible escape from the pressures of everyday life. It provides physical exercise, mental clarity, and an unparalleled connection with nature. The feeling of catching your first wave, or even just being out on the water, is something many surfers describe as a deeply transformative experience.
        </p>
    </main>
</div>